"Enjoying the Fire"
Acrylic and wax medium on paper mounted to cradled panel.
48x36"

"The Thinker"
Acrylic and wax medium on paper mounted to cradled panel. 
60x48'

This piece is a little different from the rest in how I made it. The figure is made from 12 different cut out pieces then adheded to the panel. The foreground grass was also made this way. Fun to look at in person but might not show through in the photo.

This and 16 other new works are on display today from 6-8 at @hashimotocontemporary NYC.

Taking shape.

Work coming along for my upcoming solo at @hashimotocontemporary NYC, November 11th.

I've been working on a new collection for an upcoming solo exhibition at @hashimotocontemporary NYC.
Working with 2 different concepts for the show. Part of the work is back to basics, just good old fashion oil figure painting, as seen above. The other concept is more narrative with backgrounds.
More to come!
